This project is enrolled in [clagentic-lite](https://github.com/clagentic/clagentic-lite) — a local coding harness with cross-vendor review, security gates, and session memory.

## Agents (auto-dispatched by Claude Code)

| Agent | Activates when you ask to… |
|---|---|
| `builder` | Write, edit, or refactor code |
| `reviewer` | Review staged changes or get a second opinion on code |
| `auditor` | Check for secrets, vulnerabilities, or dependency issues |
| `merge-gate` | Decide whether a change is safe to merge |

## Slash commands

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `/review` | Cross-vendor review of the staged diff |
| `/ship` | Run all gates in sequence; open a PR if green |
| `/recall` | Search session memory for prior decisions |

## Builder rules (enforced in this session)

- Work on feature branches. Do not write to `__CLAGENTIC_DEFAULT_BRANCH__` — the pre-write-guard blocks it automatically.
- Do not merge pull requests — use `/ship` instead.
- Do not review your own work — use `/review` (different vendor, different blind spots).
- Do not bypass security gates (`gitleaks`, `semgrep`, `osv-scanner`) — fix the underlying issue.

## Hooks active

Lifecycle hooks fire automatically via `.claude/settings.json`:

- **SessionStart** — injects recent session summaries as context
- **UserPromptSubmit** — keyword recall from session memory
- **PreToolUse(Bash)** — blocks dangerous shell patterns
- **PreToolUse(Write|Edit)** — blocks writes to the default branch
- **Stop** — summarizes the turn into `.clagentic/memory.db`

## Audit trail

```sh
scripts/gates.sh digest          # today's gate runs
sqlite3 .clagentic/audit.db "SELECT ts, gate, outcome FROM gate_runs ORDER BY ts DESC LIMIT 20;"
```
